    <h2>Why Remove Tree Stumps?</h2>
    <p>Old stumps are more than ugly — they attract termites, carpenter ants, and other wood-boring pests. They create tripping hazards, make mowing difficult, and can sprout new growth that's hard to kill. Stump grinding eliminates all of these problems in a single visit.</p>

    <h2>How Stump Grinding Works</h2>
    <p>Our stump grinder chips the stump and surface roots into small wood pieces, grinding 6 to 12 inches below the soil surface. The wood chips can be used as mulch in garden beds, or we haul them away — your choice. The hole is backfilled with the remaining chips and levels out naturally over a few weeks. You can plant grass, lay sod, or install landscaping right over the area.</p>

    <h2>Stump Grinding vs. Stump Removal</h2>
    <p>Grinding is faster, less invasive, and less expensive than full stump extraction. Full removal (pulling the stump and root ball out of the ground) is only necessary if you're building on the spot or need the roots gone entirely. For most residential situations, grinding is the right choice.</p>

    <h2>Stump Grinding Costs in Concord</h2>
    <p>Most residential stumps cost $100 to $500 depending on size and accessibility. We offer multi-stump discounts — if you have several to remove, the per-stump cost drops significantly.</p>
